        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Closer adjustment can be made by sanding next thicker spacer to desired thickness using emery
                    cloth on a flat surface.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Wash spacer thoroughly of emery cuttings before installing on pinion.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After proper preload is achieved, install new roll pin into forward carrier pinion. If roll
                pin cannot be installed, tighten pinion nut until roll pin can be installed. Pinion gear and cage
                assembly are now ready to be installed into the carrier housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After proper preload is achieved on rear carriers, remove end yoke, and install new seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and dry threads on pinion. Install end yoke (use service tool ZTSE 4336). Install nut
                by applying Heavy Duty Lock n' Seal&#174; to threads. Refer to GROUP - 10 LUBRICATION AND SEALER in the
                CTS-5000 Master Service Manual. Use torque multiplier and tighten nut to 900 to 1200 ft-lbs. (1220 to
                1627 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
